This paper focuses on user participation in requirements engineering, which is a key aspect of software engineering. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper discusses user-developer perception gaps, which are related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybersecurity (cs.CY) since understanding requirements is crucial for ensuring secure software. The paper also mentions top management support, which is related to social and information sciences (cs.SI) and computer engineering (cs.CE) since it involves organizational and technical aspects of software development.
